The paper deals with image inpainting using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed approach involves a generative model, which is a type of machine learning algorithm, and utilizes contextual attention, which is a form of attention mechanism commonly used in natural language processing (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on multiple datasets including faces, textures, and natural images, which suggests that it may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
